<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by dinglehopper on 12-13-2001 10:34 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">First, if you hang around these boards long enough you will see that it is a necessary evil.  If we let every radical new hothead post their ideals (especially those ideals that go against mainstream thinking) without beating them down and deflating their ego, then the board becomes overrun with them.  If you go back a ways in the archives you will see all kinds of crazy ideals, many of them much more radical than “linux is the only way to go”.  We even had someone about a month ago try and convince us that we should be using our talents to rob the bank accounts of the rich because they are leaches that don’t deserve the money they stole.  We have had several attempts to convince us to help topple either U.S. or other government computer systems because they are not socialist and should be socialist.  Those people got much worse beat downs than you did from us.  The number of incredibly stupid people on this planet is astounding.  Another reason your posts met with such hostility is about 3 or 4 weeks ago we beat the linux vs. Microsoft issue to death in what ended up being about 20 different threads.  Your friend starting a new thread when one already existed was reminiscent of that era on these boards.  

Now that you seem to be in a more reasonable mood let me give you some advice.  Do not shun microshaft.  No true programmer prefers to program in it over unix/linux, and that will likely remain true for a long time.  But, microsoft is great for the wallets of people like us.  Just think of microsoft as job security.  As long as they keep putting out programs and OS’s people like us with CS degrees will always have a job keeping it running for businesses.  The more you know about microsoft and are familiar with its errors and bugs and how to fix them, equals more money you can make.  

Bill Gates is a scoundrel, no denying that.  The worst part is the person he paid for dos was his best friend at the time.  He also already had sold the contract for dos to IBM before he ever even mentioned buying it to his friend.  And what’s worse is he flat out lied and said he was simply buying it for personal use to tinker around with, knowing he already had a multimillion dollar contract for it.  He has tried many other devious schemes as well, but I’ll leave that for you to find out about and marvel over in your own time.

Tackle life with an open mind, and life will open itself to you!
</TEXTAREA>
